LI. Cumae, May 4, 49 B.C. This is Cicero’s reply to Ep. L. A month after he wrote this letter, in which he disclaims any inten- tion of joining the Pompeians, he set out for the East. This seems to be a frank statement, however, of Cicero’s intentions at the time.
